new operator :-
used for allocating memory dynamically, calls the constructor of the data-type
int *a = new int;
int *a = new int(3);

customDataType *a = new customDataType;
customDataType *a = new customDataType(2, 3); 

int *arr = new int[N];

delete operator :-
used for deallocating memory allocated by new, calls the destructor of the data-type
delete a;
delete[] arr;
